cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.NE 

This paper is about building an open-domain multi-turn conversation system using reinforcement learning. The paper focuses on modeling the conversation flow in an ongoing dialogue, which is a key aspect of natural conversations. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also uses reinforcement learning, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of the model for long-term conversations, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.SD (Software Engineering) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
